<div id="proj-overview" class="proj-overview">
    <div id="description" class="description">
        <h3>Description:</h3>
        <p>
            A Vim colorscheme built on Steve Losh's Badwolf. Its colors can be seen all around this page, as it is also the main color palette for this website.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div id="subpages" class="subpages">
        <h3>Subpages:</h3>
        <ul class="text">
            <li>
                <a href="miamineon-vim.html">miamineon.vim</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="miamineon-al.html">miamineon-airline.vim</a>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div id="install" class="install">
        <h3>Installation:</h3>
        <p>To install miamineon, use the following commands in a linux environment:</p>
        <p>(Note: The third and fourth lines are for airline users only.)</p>
        <p>
        {% highlight raw linenos %}
git clone https://github.com/keelbeelveel/miamineon.git
mv miamineon.vim ~/.vim/colors/
mv miamineon-airline.vim \
~/.vim/plugged/vim-airline-themes/autoload/airline/themes/miamineon.vim{% endhighlight %}
        </p>
        <p>Additionally, add the following to your .vimrc file:</p>
        <p>(Note: The second line is unnecessary for non-airline users)</p>
        <p>
            {% highlight raw linenos %}
colorscheme miamineon
let g:airline_theme = 'miamineon'{% endhighlight %}
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
